Organization = {QAHE},
Abstract = {During the past few years, writer identification has attracted
   significant interest due to its real-life applications including
   document analysis, forensics etc. Machine learning algorithms have
   played an important role in the development of writer identification
   systems demonstrating very effective performance results. Recently, the
   emergence of deep learning has led to various system in computer vision
   and pattern recognition applications. Therefore, this work aims to
   assess and compare the performance between one of the deep learning
   algorithms, AlexNet model, with two of the most effective machine
   learning classification approaches: Support Vector Machine (SVM) and
   K-Nearest-Neighbour (KNN). The evaluation has been conducted using both
   IAM dataset for English handwriting and ICFHR 2012 dataset for Arabic
   handwriting.},
