   Ambient Intelligence (UCAmI), Cordoba, SPAIN, NOV 29-DEC 02, 2022},
Abstract = {Public security is a concept that, in western societies, is not given
   enough importance since the crime rates are at socially acceptable
   levels. Nowadays, with the help of artificial intelligence methods, it
   is possible to detect abnormal behaviour patterns in groups of people.
   This information can then be used to predict what is happening or about
   to happen in an event which may create a risk to public security. In
   this paper, a systematic review of artificial intelligence methods,
   essentially in deep learning and computer vision, able to detect
   gatherings of people and abnormal events is proposed. Some of the open
   research areas are identified, including the lack of works addressing
   multiple cases of anomalies in large concentrations of people, which
   leaves open an important avenue for future scientific work.},
