Abstract = {The growing population of Nigeria has subsequently led to a higher
   number of cars on the road. This has resulted in an increase in traffic
   violations and road-related crimes such as hit and run, kidnappings,
   robbery, etc. which have all contributed to road insecurity in the
   country. It has also made it increasingly difficult to keep track of
   vehicles for law enforcement and traffic management. Number plate
   recognition is still majorly carried out manually in most parts of
   Nigeria, which is neither efficient nor effective. Automatic Number
   Plate Recognition (ANPR) has therefore become an active field of study.
   ANPR technology is a means to help detect, deter and disrupt criminality
   at a local, regional and national level, which includes tackling
   traveling criminals, Organized Crime Groups and terrorists. In this
   paper, an ANPR system is proposed using Machine Learning Technique.},
