   and Communications-TRUSTCOM-Annual, Sanya, PEOPLES R CHINA, DEC 17-21,
   2024},
Organization = {Xidian University; Zhengzhou University; IEEE Computer Society},
Abstract = {With the increasing prevalence of underground cybercrime communities in
   the cyber ecosystem, identifying illegal SIM card vendors can reveal
   their organizational structure and expose their behavioral patterns,
   allowing for early warning and improving countermeasures' efficiency.
   With the rapid development of machine learning and deep learning
   technologies, natural language processing techniques have been widely
   applied. When identifying card vendors, most research has been limited
   to representing text features from a single dimension and data source.
   Therefore, we proposed a method to discover card vendor cliques based on
   multi-source data. The process includes: first, analyzing and
   constructing the card vendor ontology model to store data from the group
   chat, forum, and dialogue. Second, extract the attributes of the card
   vendor entities based on the rotary positional encoding with the BiLSTM
   model, building the intelligence database. Third, the intelligence
   database is embedded into vectors based on the GNN and autoencoder for
   further card vendor cliques discovery. After constructing the
   intelligence database consisting of 3,792 nodes and 25,602
   relationships, our method successfully discovered 12 card vendor
   cliques, which demonstrates the effectiveness of the method.},
