   E-GOVERNMENT SERVICES},
Series = {Advances in Electronic Government Digital Divide and Regional
   Development},
Year = {2015},
Pages = {20-37},
Abstract = {This chapter aims to discuss the role of Information and Communication
   Technologies (ICTs)-especially of the so-called Big Data-in the
   innovation of public service delivery. After reviewing the relevant
   literature on innovation and innovation diffusion in the public sector
   and the rise of Big Data, the chapter presents a narrative of the case
   of the adoption and implementation of predictive policing in Kent County
   Police, UK, as an instance of (early) application of Big Data in public
   sector organizations. On the whole, the analysis of the case suggests
   that past conditions and adoption strategies play an important role in
   the introduction and acceptance of innovative work practices that
   exploit the potential of contemporary ICTs.},
