   Cluster ICT; Eastern Cluster ICT; SIAM, Bulgarian Sect},
Abstract = {Several studies have shown that the use of embeddings improves outcomes
   in many Natural Language Processing (NLP) activities, including text
   categorization. This paper focuses on how word embeddings can be used on
   newspaper articles related to crimes. The scope is the categorization of
   the news articles based on the type of crime they report. We compare
   different Word2Vec models and methods to obtain word embeddings. Then,
   we exploit both supervised and unsupervised Machine Learning
   categorization algorithms. Experiments were conducted on an Italian
   dataset of 15,361 crime news articles showing very promising results.},
